message.content: To rationalize the denominator, we multiply the numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator: $$\begin{aligned} \frac{1+\sqrt{3}}{1-\sqrt{3}} &= \frac{1+\sqrt{3}}{1-\sqrt{3}}\cdot\frac{1+\sqrt{3}}{1+\sqrt{3}} \\ &= \frac{(1+\sqrt{3})(1+\sqrt{3})}{(1-\sqrt{3})(1+\sqrt{3})} \\ &= \frac{1+2\sqrt{3}+3}{1-3} \\ &= \frac{4+2\sqrt{3}}{-2} \\ &= -2-2\sqrt{3} \end{aligned}$$So $ABC=(-2)(-2)(3)=\boxed{12}$.
